This is the Perl distribution Loop-Control.

INSTALLATION

Loop-Control installation is straightforward. If your CPAN shell is
set up, you should just be able to do

    % cpan Loop::Control

Download it, unpack it, then build it as per the usual:

    % perl Makefile.PL
    % make && make test

Then install it:

    % make install

DOCUMENTATION

Loop-Control documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    % perldoc Loop::Control

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

Marcel Gruenauer
